## Part 2 — CRITICAL BUGS 🔴 (Fix Before Day 2)

### Bug 1 — Spring Boot Version `3.5.13` Does Not Exist
**File:** `pom.xml`, line 8  
**Problem:**  
```xml
<version>3.5.13</version>
```
Spring Boot `3.5.13` does not exist. As of April 2026, the latest stable releases are in the `3.2.x` / `3.3.x` / `3.4.x` lines. This version string will cause Maven to fail on first `./mvnw` run with a "Could not resolve artifact" error.

**Fix:**
```xml
<version>3.4.4</version>  <!-- or latest 3.4.x / 3.3.x stable -->
```
Verify with: https://spring.io/projects/spring-boot#learn  
Or run: `./mvnw versions:display-dependency-updates`

> [!CAUTION]
> This is a build-breaking issue. `./mvnw test` will never pass until this is corrected. Verify what version was actually used during Day 1 by checking what compiled successfully, then lock it exactly.

---

### Bug 2 — `@Where` Is Deprecated in Hibernate 6 (Spring Boot 3.x)
**File:** `Booking.java`, line 8 and 40  
**Problem:**
```java
import org.hibernate.annotations.Where;
// ...
@Where(clause = "deleted_at IS NULL")
```
`org.hibernate.annotations.Where` was deprecated in Hibernate 6.2 and removed in Hibernate 6.3+. Spring Boot 3.x ships with Hibernate 6.4+. This annotation will either produce a `ClassNotFoundException` at runtime or silently not apply the filter — both are critical failures.

**Fix — replace with `@SQLRestriction`:**
```java
import org.hibernate.annotations.SQLRestriction;
// ...
@SQLRestriction("deleted_at IS NULL")
public class Booking {
```

---

### Bug 3 — Spring State Machine 3.2.0 Is Incompatible with Spring Boot 3.x
**File:** `pom.xml`, line 72–75  
**Problem:**
```xml
<artifactId>spring-statemachine-core</artifactId>
<version>3.2.0</version>
```
Spring State Machine 3.2.0 was built against Spring Framework 5.x / Spring Boot 2.7. The project uses Spring Boot 3.x (Spring Framework 6.x). This will produce context initialization failures — most likely `NoSuchMethodError` on Spring Framework 6 APIs that SSM 3.2.0 doesn't know.

**Fix:**
```xml
<version>4.0.0</version>  <!-- First SSM release supporting Spring Boot 3.x -->
```
Spring State Machine 4.0.0 introduced Spring Boot 3.x and Spring Framework 6.x support.

> [!WARNING]  
> The `BookingStateMachineConfig` (Day 8) is architecturally the most complex component. Without SSM 4.0.0, Day 8 cannot start. Validate this fix by running `./mvnw dependency:tree` to confirm no Spring 5.x transitive dependencies remain.

---

### Bug 4 — `TicketTier` Missing `@Version` (Fix 7.1 Not Applied)
**File:** `TicketTier.java`  
**Problem:**
The constitution (Principle II) states:  
> "optimistic locking via @Version on Booking and TicketTier entities"

`Booking.java` has `@Version Long version` ✅  
`TicketTier.java` has **no `@Version` field** ❌  

Without it, two concurrent requests that update the same tier's `available_count` can race, with both reads seeing the same pre-update value and both writes committing — a classic lost-update that causes oversell.

**Fix — add to `TicketTier.java`:**
```java
@Version
@Column(nullable = false)
private Long version;
```

**And add to V4 migration:**
```sql
version BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
```
Or create a new `V10__add_ticket_tier_version.sql`:
```sql
ALTER TABLE ticket_tiers ADD COLUMN version BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0;
```

---

### Bug 5 — `TestcontainersConfiguration` Uses `:latest` Instead of Pinned Versions
**File:** `src/test/.../TestcontainersConfiguration.java`  
**Problem:**
```java
new PostgreSQLContainer<>(DockerImageName.parse("postgres:latest"))
new RabbitMQContainer(DockerImageName.parse("rabbitmq:latest"))
new GenericContainer<>(DockerImageName.parse("redis:latest"))
```

The constitution and `docker-compose.yml` mandate `postgres:17`, `redis:7`, `rabbitmq:4-management`. Using `:latest` in tests means:
- Tests could run against a different major version than production
- Redis 8 or PostgreSQL 18 changes could silently break the test suite
- The Day 5 concurrency test (`concurrentReservations_100threads_50seats_exactlyFiftySucceed`) could behave differently across versions

**Fix:**
```java
new PostgreSQLContainer<>(DockerImageName.parse("postgres:17"))
new RabbitMQContainer(DockerImageName.parse("rabbitmq:4-management"))
new GenericContainer<>(DockerImageName.parse("redis:7")).withExposedPorts(6379)
```

