## Part 9 — Overall Assessment

**Scaffold quality: 8/10**  
The domain model is clean, migrations are rigorous, and the tooling layer (instructions, agents, session prompts) is the most complete and well-structured I have seen for a self-directed AI-assisted build. The TDD loop in session prompts is correctly ordered (Red → Green → Refactor). The constitution is a genuine governance document — not boilerplate.

**The 5 critical bugs** are all fixable in under 30 minutes total and none of them indicate a design flaw — they are version/annotation migration issues from Hibernate 5→6 and SSM 2→4 ecosphere changes.

Once the P1–P5 fixes are applied and `./mvnw test` returns green (context loads, Flyway runs, Testcontainers connects), the project is genuinely ready for Day 2.

**Day 2 readiness gate:**
```
[ ] ./mvnw dependency:resolve  → no errors (version exists)
[ ] ./mvnw compile             → zero errors
[ ] ./mvnw test -Dtest=TicketingPlatformApplicationTests → context loads
[ ] @SQLRestriction in Booking (not @Where)
[ ] TicketTier.version field exists
[ ] SSM dependency is 4.0.0
[ ] TestcontainersConfiguration uses pinned versions
```
